                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12769034" author="hossman" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2009 03:57:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch demonstrating my suggestion from email ... with this config you can run the clustering example (once the dependencies are downloaded) via...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;cd example;
java -Dsolr.clustering.enabled=true -jar start.jar
http://localhost:8983/solr/clustering?indent=on&amp;amp;q=*:*&amp;amp;rows=10
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if that system property is not set, the clustering component (and the hander it&apos;s configured on) will not be initalized, so it won&apos;t matter if the jars can&apos;t be found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If people like this patch, we can also &quot;svn rm contrib/clustering/example&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12769041" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2009 04:14:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Eliminating another solrhome sounds like a good simplification to me!&lt;br/&gt;
Is &quot;enable&quot; even needed to avoid throwing an exception?  I just tried deleting the data directory and firing up the clustering example - no exceptions until I tried to actually hit it with a clustering request.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12769048" author="hossman" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2009 04:48:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The data directory?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you mean you deleted lib/download and then tried it?... that&apos;s the real issue, that they won&apos;t have the libs available.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;leaving them in w/o the system property based enable option probably would load fine and only fail if a clustering request was made, but the nice advantage of the enable property is that it prevents the component/handelr from even being listed in the registry/stats.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i&apos;m cool either way ... whichever you think makes the example less confusing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12769054" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2009 05:32:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Err, right, I deleted lib/download and there were no apparent errors if you avoided sending requests to the clustering handler.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll punt on whether the enable property should be there or not... clustering is on the edge of experimental that this point anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12769301" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 23 Oct 2009 18:07:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m +1 for committing...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12769752" author="hossman" created="Sun, 25 Oct 2009 04:39:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 829493.&lt;br/&gt;
also updated the wiki...&lt;br/&gt;
